---

# 4. Backend Architecture

The backend follows a layered architecture.

```
API Router
      │
      ▼
Service Layer
      │
      ▼
Repository Layer
      │
      ▼
Database Layer
```

Business logic must remain inside the Service Layer.

Routers should only validate requests and responses.

Repositories should only interact with the database.

---

# 5. Module Structure

Each module follows the same internal structure.

Example:

```
shipment/

router.py

service.py

repository.py

model.py

schema.py

constants.py
```

This ensures consistency across the codebase.

---

# 6. Design Principles

- Modular architecture
- Separation of concerns
- Feature-based frontend organization
- Layered backend architecture
- API-first development
- Database abstraction
- Independent AI modules
- Future microservice compatibility